{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place flaxseeds (linseeds), almonds and cashews into mixing bowl and grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides and bottom of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add all remaining ingredients, except oil, into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then mix a further <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer into a glass or ceramic bowl and set aside to rest and thicken for 30 minutes.","Lightly grease a non-stick frying pan (15 cm) with coconut oil and place over medium heat. Stir batter well, then pour a small ladle of batter into hot frying pan (approx. 2½ tbsp), swirling pan as you pour to cover the base. Fry for 1-2 minutes, or until edges of tortilla are light golden. Flip tortilla over and fry for a further 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a warm serving bowl or a plate and cover to keep warm. Repeat with remaining batter to make 16 tortillas. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 tbsp flaxseeds (linseeds)","30 g raw almonds","20 g raw cashew nuts","1 tbsp coconut flour","1 tbsp arrowroot","¼ tsp baking powder","½ tsp onion salt","8 egg whites (approx. 240 g)","250 g almond milk","coconut oil, for greasing"]}],"id":"r178521","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-2zyrY88NG6g\/XZWqrdlxc4I\/AAAAAAAAfbo\/hOeJ-w76e7MtqFosWbbA570i_J6O2NWFwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_SV6-SLJWGjnM3WLv.png","title":"Tortillas","publishedAt":"2017-05-22T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.33 g","fat":"5.139 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"1.24 g","calories":"273 kJ \/ 65 kcal"},"usefulItems":"non-stick frying pan (15 cm), serving bowl, small ladle, hob","hintsAndTricks":["Serve tortillas as part of a Mexican dinner, use as wraps for sandwiches or even slice and bake to make tortilla chips.","Save your egg yolks to use in a creamy ice cream or in a Hollandaise sauce (refer to the recipes in <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em><em><\/em>)."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 30m","16 portions"]}